China â€™s Guangdong province,  Hong
Kong  and Macau will cooperate to improve the air quality of the
Pearl River Delta region, according to a joint statement from
the local governments today.  Hong Kong and the southern Chinese province will announce a
plan to reduce air pollutant emissions for the region up to
2020, the report said. The governments may also encourage
vessels berthing at the Pearl River Delta area to use cleaner
fuel, it said.  The three areas will jointly promote the use of renewable
energy, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
